WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:09.520 --> 00:00:15.500
Cure the beef slices with seasoning mix A for 2 minutes

00:00:26.960 --> 00:00:35.900
add 1 tablespoon salad oil and set aside

00:00:46.380 --> 00:00:56.340
Clean and layout the Chinese kale leaves, pare them for use

00:00:57.900 --> 00:01:05.200
Heat the frying pan, add a little oil and ginger until the aroma emerges

00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:11.320
Put in Chinese broccoli,

00:01:11.320 --> 00:01:21.800
add 2 tablespoons water, 1 tablespoon rice wine, salt and 1 teaspoon of sugar and a pinch of salt

00:01:29.320 --> 00:01:38.300
stir-fry until the vegetables soften

00:01:46.240 --> 00:01:58.200
When they are  cooked drain and remove, placing them in a row along the bottom of the plate.

00:02:12.480 --> 00:02:18.060
Wash out the pot, add 2 tablespoons oil

00:02:19.420 --> 00:02:29.400
the beef mixture and stir over a low flame until the beef turns white

00:02:34.120 --> 00:02:38.880
over low heat cook the ginger and green onions until fragrant

00:02:38.880 --> 00:02:54.300
add hot peppers, fresh mushrooms, oyster sauce and water, stirring evenly

00:03:05.360 --> 00:03:15.300
fry on high heat for 10 seconds . Afterwards add cornstarch to the water to thicken it

